1
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,770
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:01:38,770 --> 00:01:41,723
[Episode Five]

3
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,456
The roots of popularising science and democracy

4
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:47,080
lie in education.

5
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,776
If you, Cai Yuanpei,

6
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:52,376
can use the treasure of Peking University to reform and innovate

7
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:54,456
in order to revive our Chinese nation,

8
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:57,320
you will have our support and hope.

9
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:03,096
The words of Brother Botang

10
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:07,256
are exactly what I, Cai Yuanpei, want.

11
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:09,816
Okay, I'm going to reply to Li Yuanhong

12
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:13,080
to take up his post at Peking University as soon as possible.

13
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,456
Hold on, Brother Jiemin.

14
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:20,376
If you want this job, you have to do it right.

15
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:22,536
Without water, it's hard to build a canal.

16
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,376
If you want to be in this hornet's nest of Peking University,

17
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,376
and make a career out of it.

18
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:29,880
It's going to take a lot of work!

19
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:32,616
Please teach me, Brother Botang.

20
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:34,136
I know you have a well-developed idea

21
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:36,456
of how to revolutionize education,

22
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,936
but in order to achieve your ambition,

23
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:42,376
you have to meet the conditions set by Li Yuanhong:

24
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,976
sufficient funds,

25
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,416
abundance of talented people,

26
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,856
transfer of power to lower level.

27
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,376
Without these three demands,

28
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:51,640
no matter how good your plans are

29
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:54,136
as the old Beijing saying goes

30
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:56,760
it will be "a blind waste of time".

31
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:03,960
With Brother Botang's help, I, Yuanpei,

32
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:07,785
am certain to become the president of Peking University.

33
00:03:07,809 --> 00:03:09,799
Good.

34
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,680
Excellent, excellent!

35
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:15,213
{\an8}[Yadong Library, Shanghai]

36
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,455
The young are promising!

37
00:03:15,479 --> 00:03:17,016
The young are promising!

38
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:20,856
This Hu Shizhi fired eight bombshells at once,

39
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,496
each hitting the lifeblood of old literature.

40
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,856
Baisha, hurry up and arrange

41
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:27,840
the official 1917 New Year's publication

42
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:27,896
{\an8}[Yi Baisha, styled Yuecun, scholar of the New Culture Movement]
{\an8}[Wang Mengzou, manager of Yadong Library]

43
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,200
of "New Youth" to China

44
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,848
{\an8}[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhongfu, editor-in-chief of "New Youth"]

45
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,496
as a New Year's gift.

46
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,016
Zhongfu, take it easy, don't rush.

47
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,216
Didn't we agree?

48
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:36,936
The first issue will publish Hu Shi's eight vernacular poems.

49
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,776
You can't make it a special issue.

50
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,896
Besides, he's a nobody,

51
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,736
few people in China know him.

52
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:44,296
If he does not sell, we can not afford the loss.

53
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:45,336
Put the vernacular poem further back.

54
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:48,200
This article "A Preliminary Discussion of Language Reform" is more influential.

55
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:50,376
Wait, why has it changed to "Reform?"

56
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,656
Isn't it a revolution?

57
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,256
This carries a lot less weight.

58
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,936
Is this kid scared?

59
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,616
It's understandable that young people have their worries.

60
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,216
If he wants "Reform" so be it.

61
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:00,616
I'll write him an editor's note on this one,

62
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:03,336
and I'll write the "On Literary Revolution" on the next one.

63
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:05,336
Yes, the New Culture Movement's

64
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,296
flag-bearer

65
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:08,936
should be a famous person like you, Chen Zhongfu.

66
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,856
It's enough for the younger generation

67
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,456
to just lead the charge.

68
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:13,416
Mengzou.

69
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,936
This "New Youth" is becoming more and more influential

70
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,456
and the distribution must keep up.

71
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,776
Especially in schools and in some big cities

72
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,776
that have to become our main battlefield.

73
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:23,176
I was just about to discuss the prospectus with you.

74
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,936
Beijing has a lot of cultural businessmen,

75
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,696
who are very optimistic about "New Youth".

76
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,696
and about you, Chen Duxiu,

77
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,616
and they all wanted to actively invest in the venture.

78
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,136
We must go to Beijing in the near future.

79
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,216
Good, I'd love to check it out.

80
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,376
If the New Culture Movement is not active in Beijing,

81
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,896
could it be even called a movement?

82
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:40,616
If no one in Beijing shows up to support "New Youth",

83
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:41,896
does it have any influence?

84
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,256
I think this can not be delayed.

85
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:45,444
Next week, next week we will leave.

86
00:04:45,468 --> 00:04:46,039
Next week?

87
00:04:46,039 --> 00:04:47,336
Next week.

88
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,880
Alright, alright.

89
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,424
"New Youth"!

90
00:05:06,424 --> 00:05:09,404
Read the newly published "New Youth"!

91
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:12,638
"New Youth"!

92
00:05:12,662 --> 00:05:12,823
"New Youth"!

93
00:05:12,823 --> 00:05:13,623
Read the newly published "New Youth"!

94
00:05:13,623 --> 00:05:15,703
Read "New Youth"!

95
00:05:16,429 --> 00:05:18,705
Read the newly published "New Youth"!

96
00:05:18,729 --> 00:05:20,308
Read the newly published "New Youth"!

97
00:05:20,308 --> 00:05:21,805
"New Youth"!

98
00:05:21,829 --> 00:05:24,998
Read the newly published "New Youth"!

99
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:30,760
Newly published "New Youth"!

100
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,440
You go back first.

101
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,816
What does this mean?

102
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:52,056
Count it. Two dollars and eighty-six cents.

103
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,360
We dried out the magazines.

104
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,696
No need for this.

105
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:58,536
You still don't want?

106
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,576
How about this?

107
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:02,200
Count me in to buy thirteen of your magazines.

108
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,376
Sold.

109
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,416
Qiaonian.

110
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:07,736
Wrap thirteen magazines for this sister.

111
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,720
That's right!

112
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,816
Actually I had a big fight with my dad

113
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,576
that day at home.

114
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,376
When I got up in the morning,

115
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,976
there was no one at home.

116
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,536
I was late when no one asked me to go to school.

117
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,856
So I was in a bad mood that day.

118
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,376
My attitude was naturally bad.

119
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:33,000
So I kicked you all out in a rage.

120
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,536
Don't take it personally.

121
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,736
We made mistakes before

122
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,336
not knowing the school rules.

123
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:39,416
I also changed your bucket of water.

124
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,856
We both apologize to you.

125
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,199
Don't take it to heart.

126
00:06:42,223 --> 00:06:43,176
Don't take it to heart.

127
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,456
Then we will not take it to heart.

128
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,527
We're even.

129
00:06:45,551 --> 00:06:47,381
Even.

130
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,856
So what you are saying is

131
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:56,616
you would like me to go to America with Liu Mei.

132
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,600
Correct.

133
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,136
And for your brother,

134
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,896
if you agree,

135
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,656
I'll ask Mr. Wu Zhihui

136
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:06,536
to apply for your quotas in the Ministry of Education.

137
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:09,336
But we can't accept other people's funding.

138
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,696
You misunderstood this.

139
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,936
I'm not trying to fund you.

140
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:15,416
I want you to do me a favor.

141
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,496
Liu Mei is my only daughter.

142
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,256
She is still young now

143
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:21,416
and has poor ability to live independently.

144
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:24,296
If she goes to study alone,

145
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:26,056
I won't feel at ease.

146
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:29,416
But if you go with her,

147
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:31,896
you will take care of each other.

148
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,496
I'll be relieved.

149
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,896
And as far as the current situation is concerned,

150
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:39,416
studying in the United States is the best choice.

151
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,616
This is for you both,

152
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,496
I think, a good thing.

153
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,976
Uncle, I have my own principles.

154
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,600
We cannot accept this kindness of yours.

155
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,760
Farewell for now.

156
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,463
Yannian.

157
00:07:56,623 --> 00:07:57,896
Yannian.

158
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:00,776
Don't answer me so hastily.

159
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,856
You have to think about it.

160
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,216
But remember,

161
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:06,296
this road I've paved for you,

162
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,456
it is definitely wide,

163
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,376
it is definitely flat,

164
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:13,656
it is definitely full of sunlight.

165
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,640
Uncle.

166
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,496
I can reply to you now.

167
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:20,600
We will walk our own road.

168
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,560
Brother Jiemin, please!

169
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:38,794
{\an8}[Ministry of Education, Republic of China]

170
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:36,776
I missed you so much.

171
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:37,896
Jingsheng!

172
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:40,616
I'm forunate to have you as a friend looking out for me.

173
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,696
Otherwise,

174
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:45,240
I wouldn't have been able to come back to Beijing.

175
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,240
To welcome you, Brother Jiemin,

176
00:08:47,631 --> 00:08:48,649
{\an8}[Cai Yuanpei, styled Jiemin]

177
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:50,640
I specially prepared a Red Daughter (brand of speciality wine).

178
00:08:49,183 --> 00:08:50,936
{\an8}[Fan Yuanlian, styled Jingsheng, Minister of Education]

179
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,336
Tonight, let's get drunk.

180
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,976
Jingsheng, let's get down to business.

181
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,960
Don't get drunk later and delay business.

182
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:02,856
OK, then let's get down to business.

183
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:05,736
Brother Jiemin, Li Yuanhong has made up his mind

184
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,656
to invite you to join Peking University.

185
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,256
Six hundred dollars a month.

186
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:12,056
What do you think? When will you take office?

187
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,336
As far as I know,

188
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,440
the enthusiasm of the capital's academic community for the return of Brother Jiemin

189
00:09:14,424 --> 00:09:16,608
{\an8}[Tang Erhe, President of Beijing Medical College]

190
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,856
has never been higher!

191
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:18,376
Don't let down

192
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,936
the kindness of Brother Jingsheng.

193
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,960
Yesterday, someone set off firecrackers in North Square of Peking University,

194
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:23,164
{\an8}[Shen Yinmo, Professor at Peking University]

195
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,440
reportedly to "Welcome President Cai"!

196
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:29,736
To tell the truth,

197
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:32,296
I've repeatedly weighted the pros and cons before coming

198
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,456
and listened to the views of many people.

199
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:37,896
The fact I am in Beijing should make my true feelings self-evident.

200
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:40,056
I don't need to say too many of these polite words.

201
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:42,216
It's that, Jingsheng,

202
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:46,456
if President Li approves of my prelminary agreement,

203
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:49,816
then I'll be the president of Peking University.

204
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:53,160
Brother, please tell me about your rules.

205
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:05,176
This is my entire vision.

206
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,480
Please let me show it to you.

207
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:18,376
Brother Jiemin.

208
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:22,296
Well, this precedent you're setting is a bit too ambitious.

209
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,816
What's wrong, Jingsheng?

210
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,896
It scares the hell out of you?

211
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:29,576
And this is just my initial vision for the school.

212
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,296
The second planning scheme of the school...

213
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,496
Wait, wait, wait.

214
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:37,816
Brother Jiemin, just the first stage, recruiting talent...

215
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:38,936
You want to, from at home and abroad,

216
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:41,496
recruit a hundred professors.

217
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:45,176
Arts and sciences director, monthly salary of three hundred silver dollars.

218
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:48,776
Other professors range from one hundred and twenty to two hundred and eighty.

219
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:51,576
How much does it cost to pay the head fee for a year?

220
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:54,536
It is equivalent to dozens of times the current Peking University.

221
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:57,096
You're demanding a pound of flesh from President Li.

222
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:59,896
Jingsheng, national modernisation

223
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:02,136
must be education-oriented.

224
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,456
This is a prerequisite for financial security,

225
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:08,216
You did not recall me to the country

226
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,856
to Peking University to be a business-as-usual president.

227
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:14,520
Is this the original intention of President Li?

228
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:17,016
Such a big country

229
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:19,656
would not be short of this funding for Peking University, would it?

230
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:20,856
Minister Fan,

231
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:23,880
just talk to President Li.

232
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:28,056
Fine. Then I'll go to Li Yuanhong.

233
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:32,280
Good. Jingsheng, my regards.

234
00:11:32,356 --> 00:11:36,398
{\an8}[Qianmen Chinese-Western Hotel, Beijing]

235
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,336
Zhongfu.

236
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,096
You should listen to me.

237
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,616
Open a suite for youself.

238
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,456
You can't be too shabby when you're talking to people.

239
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,496
No need to put up a show.

240
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,616
Just a single room is enough.

241
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,056
The people coming to talk about investment are cultured.

242
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,176
They wouldn't pay attention to this.

243
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,296
Just save as much as you can.

244
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:47,176
You two be careful, here it is.

245
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,256
No. The people at the foot of the emperor

246
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,856
are all concerned about the show.

247
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,056
I can't let you,

248
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:55,240
the famous Chen Duxiu of China, lose face.

249
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,376
Buddy,

250
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:58,216
Give us a suite.

251
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:58,936
No need, no need.

252
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,776
Listen to me, just two single rooms.

253
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:01,976
What are you talking about?

254
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:04,456
If he thinks I'm poor, I won't let him join the business.

255
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,696
Brother Mengzou, no need to be fussy about accommodations.

256
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:07,896
But good food is a must.

257
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:08,616
Buddy,

258
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,096
you say,

259
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:09,976
Are there any good

260
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,416
mutton hotpot restaurants around here

261
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,616
that you can recommend?

262
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,216
Yes, right around the corner.

263
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:16,376
But at this time, it's all for the rickshaw pullers.

264
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,216
You two look like respectable people.

265
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,736
Here, you take a few more steps.

266
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:22,376
Not far to the north is Dong Lai Shun.

